st]], Canadian animator, director, and producer\n*  1959   &ndash; [[Tony Wakeford]], English singer-songwriter and guitarist \n*[[1960]] &ndash; [[Stephen Daldry]], English director and producer\n*[[1961]] &ndash; [[Steve James (snooker player)|Steve James]], English snooker player\n*  1961   &ndash; [[Sophie Thibault]], Canadian journalist\n*  1961   &ndash; [[Phil Vickery (chef)|Phil Vickery]], English chef and author\n*[[1962]] &ndash; [[Elizabeth Berridge (actress)|Elizabeth Berridge]], American actress\n*  1962   &ndash; [[Michael Grandage]], English director and producer\n*  1962   &ndash; [[Jimmy White]], English snooker player\n*[[1965]] &ndash; [[F\u00e9lix Jos\u00e9]], Dominican-American baseball player\n*[[1966]] &ndash; [[Uwe Freiler]], German footballer\n*  1966   &ndash; [[Margus Kolga]], Estonian diplomat\n*  1966   &ndash; [[Belinda Stronach]], Canadian businesswoman, philanthropist, and politician\n*[[1967]] &ndash; [[Bengt \u00c5kerblom]], Swedish ice hockey player (d. 1995)\n*  1967   &ndash; [[Mika Brzezinski]], American journalist and author\n*  1967   &ndash; [[David Rocastle]], English footballer (d. 2001)\n*[[1968]] &ndash; [[Jeff Agoos]], Swiss-American soccer player, manager, and sportscaster\n*  1968   &ndash; [[Julia Hartley-Brewer]], English broadcaster and columnist\n*  1968   &ndash; [[Ziana Zain]], Malaysian singer-songwriter and actress\n*[[1969]] &ndash; [[Brian Lara]], Trinidadian cricketer\n*[[1970]] &ndash; [[Marco Walker]], Swiss footballer and coach\n*[[1971]] &ndash; [[Musashimaru K\u014dy\u014d]], Samoan-American sumo wrestler, the 67th [[Makuuchi#Yokozuna|Yokozuna]]\n*  1971   &ndash; [[Fatima Yusuf]], Nigerian sprinter\n*[[1972]] &ndash; [[Paul Adcock]], English footballer\n*  1972   &ndash; [[Ahti Heinla]], Estonian programmer and businessman, co-developed [[Skype]]\n*  1972   &ndash; [[Dwayne Johnson]], American-Canadian wrestler, actor, and producer\n*[[1973]] &ndash; [[Florian Henckel von Donnersmarck]], German directo