 Bormann]], German politician (b. 1900)\n*  1945   &ndash; [[Joe Corbett]], American baseball player and journalist (b. 1875)\n*[[1947]] &ndash; [[Dorothea Binz]], German [[SS]] officer (b. 1920)\n*[[1953]] &ndash; [[Wallace Bryant (archer)|Wallace Bryant]], American archer (b. 1863)\n*[[1957]] &ndash; [[Joseph McCarthy]], American captain, lawyer, judge, and politician (b. 1908)\n*[[1963]] &ndash; [[Ronald Barnes, 3rd Baron Gorell]], English cricketer, peer, politician, poet, author and newspaper editor (b. 1884)\n*[[1964]] &ndash; [[Nancy Astor, Viscountess Astor]], American-English politician (b. 1879)\n*[[1969]] &ndash; [[Franz von Papen]], German general and politician, [[Chancellor of Germany (German Reich)|Chancellor of Germany]] (b. 1879)\n*[[1972]] &ndash; [[J. Edgar Hoover]], American 1st [[director of the Federal Bureau of Investigation]] (b. 1895)\n*[[1974]] &ndash; [[James O. Richardson]], American admiral (b. 1878)\n*[[1977]] &ndash; [[Nicholas Magallanes]], American principal dancer and charter member of the [[New York City Ballet]] (b. 1922)\n*[[1979]] &ndash; [[Giulio Natta]], Italian chemist and engineer, [[Nobel Prize in Chemistry|Nobel Prize]] laureate (b. 1903)\n*[[1980]] &ndash; [[Clarrie Grimmett]], New Zealand-Australian cricketer (b. 1891)\n*  1980   &ndash; [[George Pal]], Hungarian-American animator and producer (b. 1908)\n*[[1983]] &ndash; [[Norm Van Brocklin]], American football player and coach (b. 1926)\n*[[1984]] &ndash; [[Jack Barry (game show host)|Jack Barry]], American game show host and producer, co-founded [[Barry & Enright Productions]] (b. 1918)\n*  1984   &ndash; [[Bob Clampett]], American animator, director, and producer (b. 1913)\n*[[1985]] &ndash; [[Attilio Bettega]], Italian race car driver (b. 1951)\n*  1985   &ndash; [[Larry Clinton]], American trumpet player and bandleader (b. 1909)\n*[[1986]] &ndash; [[Sergio Cresto]], American race car driver (b. 1956)\n*  1986   &ndash; [[Henri Toivonen]], Finnish race car driver (b. 1956)\n*[[1989]] &ndash; [[Veniamin Kaverin]], Russian author (b. 1902)\n*  1989   &ndash; [[Giuseppe Siri]], Italian cardinal (b. 1906)\n*[[1990]] &ndash; [[David Rappaport]], English-American actor (b. 1951)\n*[[1991]] &ndash; [[Gauri Shankar Rai]], Indian Politician(b.1924)\n*  1991   &ndash; [[Ronald McKie]], Australian journalist and author (b. 1909)\n*[[1992]] &ndash; [[Wilbur Mills]], American lawyer and politician (b. 1909)\n*[[1993]] &ndash; [[Andr\u00e9 Moynet]], French race car driver, pilot, and politician (b. 1921)\n*[[1994]] &ndash; [[Dorothy Marie Donnelly]], American poet and author (b. 1903)\n*[[1995]] &ndash; [[John Bunting (diplomat)|John Bunting]], Australian public servant and diplomat,  (b. 1918)\n*  1995   &ndash; [[Michael Hordern]], English actor (b. 1911)\n*[[1997]] &ndash; [[John Eccles (neurophysiologist)|John Eccles]], Australian neurophysiologist and academic, [[Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine|Nobel Prize]] laureate (b. 1903)\n*  1997   &ndash; [[Paulo Freire]], Brazilian philosopher and academic (b. 1921)\n*[[1998]] &ndash; [[hide (musician)|hide]], Japanese singer-songwriter, guitarist, and producer (b. 1964)\n*  1998   &ndash; [[Justin Fashanu]], English footballer (b. 1961)\n*  1998   &ndash; [[Gene Raymond]], American actor (b. 1908)\n*[[1999]] &ndash; [[Douglas Harkness]], Canadian colonel and politician (b. 1903)\n*  1999   &ndash; [[Oliver Reed]], English actor (b. 1938)\n* [[2000]]   &ndash; [[Sundar Popo]], [[Indo-Trinidadian]] musician (b. 1943)\n*[[2002]] &ndash; [[W. T. Tutte]], English-Canadian mathematician and academic (b. 1917)\n*[[2005]] &ndash; [[Wee Kim Wee]], Singaporean journalist and politician, 4th [[President of Singapore]] (b. 1915)\n*[[2006]] &ndash; [[Louis Rukeyser]], American journalist and author (b. 1933)\n*[[2007]] &ndash; [[Brad McGann]], New Zealand director and screenwriter (b. 1964)\n*[[2008]] &ndash; [[Beverlee McKinsey]], American actress (b. 1940)\n*  2008   &ndash; [[Izold Pust\u00f5lnik]], Ukrainian-Estonian astronomer and academic (b. 1938)\n*[[2009]] &ndash; [[Marilyn French]], American author and academic (b. 1929)\n*  2009   &ndash; [[Kiyoshiro Imawano]], Japanese singer-songwriter, producer, and actor (b. 1951)\n*  2009   &ndash; [[Jack Kemp]], American football player and politician, 9th [[United States Secretary of Housing and Urban Development]] (b. 1935)\n*[[2010]] &ndash; [[Lynn Redgrave]], English-American actress and singer (b. 1943)\n<!--Do NOT remove death notice for bin Laden, please: death was early in the morning 2 May in Pakistan local time-->\n*[[2011]] &ndash; [[Osama bin Laden]], Saudi Arabian terrorist, founder of [[Al-Qaeda]] (b. 1957)\n*[[2012]] &ndash; [[Fernando Lopes (filmmaker)|Fernando Lopes]], Portuguese director and screenwriter (b. 1935)\n*  2012   &ndash; [[Zenaida Manfug\u00e1s]], Cuban-born American-naturalized pianist (b. 1932)<ref name=\"Marti\">[http://www.martinoticias.com/content/muere_zenaida_manfugaz/10876.html Marti Noticias]. Retrieved 15, August, 2012, to 14:38 pm</ref>\n*  2012   &ndash; [[Tufan Mi\u00f1nullin]], Russian playwright and politician (b. 1936)\n*  2012   &ndash; [[Endang Rahayu Sedyaningsih]], Indonesian physician and politician, [[Ministry of Health (Indonesia)|Indonesian Minister of Health]] (b. 1955)\n*  2012   &ndash; [[Akira Tonomura]], Japanese physicist, author, and academic (b. 1942)\n*[[2013]] &ndash; [[Ernie Field]], English boxer (b. 1943)\n*  2013   &ndash; [[Jeff Hanneman]], American guitarist and songwriter (b. 1964)\n*  2013   &ndash; [[Joseph P. McFadden]], American bishop (b. 1947)\n*  2013   &ndash; [[Dvora Omer]], Israeli author and educator (b. 1932)\n*  2013   &ndash; [[Ivan Turina]], Croatian footballer (b. 1980)\n*  2013   &ndash; [[Charles Banks Wilson]], American painter and illustrator (b. 1918)\n*[[2014]] &ndash; [[Tom\u00e1s Balduino]], Brazilian bishop (b. 1922)\n*  2014   &ndash; [[\u017darko Petan]], Slovenian director, playwright, and screenwriter (b. 1929)\n