ip]].\n\n== Major results ==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" cellspacing=\"2\" cellpadding=\"5\" style=\"font-size: 95%;\"\n|- bgcolor=\"cccccc\"\n!Year\n!Tournament\n!Location\n!Result\n!Event\n|-\n|2019\n|[[2019 World Wrestling Championships|World Championships]]\n|{{flagicon|KAZ}} [[Nur-Sultan]], [[Kazakhstan]]\n|align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"silver\" | 2nd\n|[[2019 World Wrestling Championships \u2013 Men's freestyle 61 kg|Freestyle 61 kg]]\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{sports links}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Idrisov, Magomedrasul}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1996 births]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Russian male sport wrestlers]]\n[[Category:World Wrestling Championships medalists]]\n\n\n{{Russia-wrestling-bio-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Simeon", "label": "safe", "comment": "minor change", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Magomedrasul_Idrisov"}
{"title_page": "Alberto L\u00f3pez de Munain", "text_new": "{{short description|Spanish cyclist}}\n{{Infobox cyclist\n| name           = Alberto L\u00f3pez de Munain\n| image          =\n| image_size     =\n| caption        =\n| fullname       = Alberto L\u00f3pez de Munain Ruiz de Gauna\n| nickname       =\n| birth_date     = {{bda|1972|12|5|df=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[Vitoria-Gasteiz]], Spain\n| height         =\n| weight         =\n| currentteam    = Retired\n| discipline     = Road\n| role           = Rider\n| ridertype      =\n| amateuryears1  =\n| amateurteam1   =\n| amateuryears2  =\n| amateurteam2   =\n| proyears1      = 1996\u20132005\n| proteam1       = {{ct|EUS|1996}}\n| proyears2      =\n| proteam2       =\n| majorwins      =\n| medaltemplates =\n| show-medals    =\n}}\n'''Alberto L\u00f3pez de Munain Ruiz de Gauna''' (born December 5, 1972) is a [[Spain|Spanish]] former professional [[road bicycle racer]]. He became professional in 1996 and ended his professional career in 2005. He rode his entire career for the {{ct|EUS}} team. \n\nDuring the [[2005 Giro d'Italia]], he suffered a terrible crash on stage two, and was diagnosed with a [[hydropneumothorax]] caused by nine broken ribs, a broken left [[clavicle]], a broken shoulder blade and damage to his left shoulder.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/news/lopez-de-munain-back-in-spain |title=Lopez De Munain back in Spain |author=Trevorrow, John |date=May 16, 2005 |work=cyclingnews.com |accessdate=December 20, 2010}}</ref> He did not race professionally afterwards. <ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.procyclingstats.com/rider.php?id=114899 |title=Alberto L\u00f3pez de Munain |work=procyclingstats.com |accessdate=August 7, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Major results==\n{{div col}}\n;1997\n: 8th Overall [[Euskal Bizikleta]]\n;1999\n: 6th [[Subida al Naranco]]\n;2000\n: 1st Prologue [[2000 Crit\u00e9rium du Dauphin\u00e9 Lib\u00e9r\u00e9|Crit\u00e9rium du Dauphin\u00e9 Lib\u00e9r\u00e9]]\n: 2nd Overall [[Vuelta a Asturias]]\n::1st Stage 1\n;2001\n: 1st Stage 5 [[Vuelta a Asturias]]\n: 1st Stage 2 [[Cl\u00e1sica de Alcobendas]]\n;2003\n: 3rd [[Subida al Naranco]]\n: 3rd [[Subida a Urkiola]]\n: 10th Overall [[2003 Crit\u00e9rium du Dauphin\u00e9 Lib\u00e9r\u00e9|Crit\u00e9rium du Dauphin\u00e9 Lib\u00e9r\u00e9]]\n;2004\n: 7th Overall [[2004 Volta a Catalunya|Volta a Catalunya]]\n{{colend}}\n\n===Grand Tour general classification results timeline===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | [[Grand Tour (cycling)|Grand Tour]]\n! scope=\"col\" | 1999\n! scope=\"col\" | 2000\n! scope=\"col\" | 2001\n! scope=\"col\" | 2002\n! scope=\"col\" | 2003\n! scope=\"col\" | 2004\n! scope=\"col\" | 2005\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"row\" | [[File:Jersey pink.svg|20px|link=|alt=A pink jersey]] [[General classification in the Giro d'Italia|Giro d'Italia]]\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|[[2005 Giro d'Italia|DNF]]\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"row\" | [[File:Jersey yellow.svg|20px|link=|alt=A yellow jersey]] [[General classification in the Tour de France|Tour de France]]\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|[[2001 Tour de France|77]]\n|\u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|[[2003 Tour de France|98]]\n|\u2014\n|\u2014\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"row\" | [[File:Jersey red.svg|20px|link=|alt=A red jersey]] [[List of Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a general classification winners|Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|[[1999 Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a|71]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|[[2000 Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a|30]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|[[2001 Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a|129]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|[[2002 Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a|65]]\n|\u2014\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|[[2004 Vuelta a Espa\u00f1a|91]]\n|\u2014\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ Legend\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \u2014\n| Did not compete\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | [[Did Not Finish|DNF